data.reddit:
Age: 22 

Sex: Female 

Weight: 130 lbs 

Height: 5 2 

Race: white 

Primary complaint: my hearing seems to be getting worse. Over the last year I have had to start using subtitles more and more. It stared on just Netflix and tv shows every once in a while. Now it’s YouTube and every show or movie I watch. 

I can’t hear if more than one person is talking in a room or there is music too loud. It just sounds like a gumbled mess. On the phone I have to really concentrate to understand sometimes as even on the loudest setting where my mom can hear across the room, I still can’t hear. 

I used to listen to loud music as a kid, but I don’t anymore. I don’t go to concerts or anything like that so I don’t know why this is happening. 

I do have fibromyalgia, arthritis, asthma, chronic gastritis, migraines and syringomyelia (all diagnosed by medial professionals). 

I currently take these medications: 

1. Topiramate 100 mg 
2. Venlafaxine ER 75 mg (2 pills) 
3. Omeprazole 20 mg (2 pills) 
4. Sprintec TAB 
5. Benedryl (2-3 pills) 

I drink sometimes but not a lot and do not smoke. And do no recreational drugs. 

Thank you in advance
